            <div class="policy-body">
                <span class="last-updated"><i class="bi bi-calendar-event"></i> Last updated: November 10, 2025</span>

                <div class="highlight-box"><p><strong>Important:</strong> Auto ISP Billing is a software-as-a-service (SaaS) platform. As a digital service, refunds are handled differently than physical products. Please read this policy carefully before subscribing.</p></div>

                <div class="stat-row">
                    <div class="stat-pill"><div class="big">14 days</div><div class="small">Free trial</div></div>
                    <div class="stat-pill"><div class="big">30 days</div><div class="small">Money-back guarantee</div></div>
                    <div class="stat-pill"><div class="big">5&ndash;7 days</div><div class="small">Refund processing</div></div>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s1"><span class="num">01</span> Overview</h3>
                    <p>At Auto ISP Billing, we strive to provide the best ISP management software and customer satisfaction. This Refund &amp; Return Policy outlines the circumstances under which refunds may be issued and the process for requesting them.</p>
                    <p>By subscribing to Auto ISP Billing, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this policy.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s2"><span class="num">02</span> Free trial period</h3>
                    <p>We offer a <strong>14-day free trial</strong> for new users to evaluate our platform before committing to a paid subscription.</p>
                    <h4>2.1 Trial features</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access to all core features</li>
                        <li>Limited to 10 test customers</li>
                        <li>No payment information required</li>
                        <li>No automatic billing after trial ends</li>
                        <li>Full technical support during trial</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>2.2 Trial conversion</h4>
                    <p>After the trial period, you can choose to subscribe to a paid plan. Your trial data will be retained and accessible in your paid account.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s3"><span class="num">03</span> Refund eligibility</h3>
                    <h4>3.1 30-Day money-back guarantee</h4>
                    <p>We offer a <strong>30-day money-back guarantee</strong> for first-time subscribers. If you are not satisfied with Auto ISP Billing within the first 30 days of your initial paid subscription, you may request a full refund.</p>
                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <p><strong>Conditions for 30-day refund:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Must be a first-time paid subscriber</li>
                            <li>Request must be made within 30 days of initial payment</li>
                            <li>Applies to monthly or annual subscriptions</li>
                            <li>Does not apply to renewal payments</li>
                            <li>Account must not have violated Terms of Service</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <h4>3.2 Service failure refunds</h4>
                    <p>You may be eligible for a prorated refund if:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Extended downtime:</strong> Platform is unavailable for more than 48 consecutive hours due to our fault</li>
                        <li><strong>Critical feature failure:</strong> Core billing or payment features are non-functional for more than 72 hours</li>
                        <li><strong>Data loss:</strong> We are unable to restore your data due to our system failure (rare, as we maintain multiple backups)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>3.3 Billing errors</h4>
                    <p>If you were charged incorrectly due to a billing system error, we will issue a full refund for the erroneous charge within 5-7 business days.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s4"><span class="num">04</span> Non-refundable situations</h3>
                    <div class="highlight-box warn"><p>Refunds will <strong>NOT</strong> be issued in the following cases:</p></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Renewal payments:</strong> Subscription renewals (monthly or annual) are non-refundable</li>
                        <li><strong>Partial month usage:</strong> No prorated refunds for partial month cancellations</li>
                        <li><strong>Change of mind:</strong> After the 30-day guarantee period, refunds are not issued for change of mind</li>
                        <li><strong>Lack of usage:</strong> Not using the platform does not qualify for a refund</li>
                        <li><strong>Feature expectations:</strong> Refunds are not issued if the platform doesn&rsquo;t meet your specific expectations (use the free trial to evaluate)</li>
                        <li><strong>Third-party costs:</strong> Costs for third-party services (SMS, WhatsApp, payment gateway fees) are non-refundable</li>
                        <li><strong>Terms violation:</strong> Accounts suspended or terminated for violating Terms of Service</li>
                        <li><strong>Upgrade/downgrade:</strong> Changing subscription plans does not qualify for refunds</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s5"><span class="num">05</span> Subscription cancellation</h3>
                    <h4>5.1 How to cancel</h4>
                    <p>You can cancel your subscription at any time through:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Account Settings &rarr; Subscription &rarr; Cancel Subscription</li>
                        <li>Contacting support at <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a></li>
                        <li>Calling {{ support_phone }}</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>5.2 Cancellation effect</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period</li>
                        <li>You retain access until the paid period expires</li>
                        <li>No refund for the remaining days in the current billing period</li>
                        <li>Automatic renewal is disabled</li>
                        <li>You have 30 days to export your data after cancellation</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>5.3 Reactivation</h4>
                    <p>You can reactivate your account within 90 days of cancellation. After 90 days, your data will be permanently deleted.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s6"><span class="num">06</span> Refund request process</h3>
                    <h4>6.1 How to request a refund</h4>
                    <p>To request a refund, follow these steps:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Email <a href="mailto:support@autoispbilling.com">support@autoispbilling.com</a> with subject &ldquo;Refund Request&rdquo;</li>
                        <li>Include your account details (Company ID, Admin ID, registered email)</li>
                        <li>Provide reason for refund request</li>
                        <li>Include transaction ID or payment receipt</li>
                        <li>Specify preferred refund method</li>
                    </ol>
                    <h4>6.2 Refund processing time</h4>
                    <ul>
